sub_topic: Prove that the complement of a set is unique.
message_1: Let A be a set such that A = {3, 6, 9, 12, 15}. Determine the unique complement of this set.
message_2:
To determine the unique complement of set A, we need to know the universal set U, which contains all the elements under consideration. The complement of set A, denoted as A', is the set of all elements in the universal set U that are not in set A.

Please provide the universal set U or the range of elements under consideration.
